a. std::cin >> int input_value
Wrong: Need to define input_value first.
Answer: int input_value; std::cin >> input_value;
b. int i = {3.14};
Wrong: List initialization doesn't allow conversion that might lead to the loss of information.
Answer: int i = 3.14;
c. double salary = wage = 9999.99;
Wrong: wage is not defined.
Answer: double salary, wage; salary = wage = 9999.99;
d. int i = 3.14;
Correct: i will be 3
